<document><title><tag>table</tag> component</title>

<section><title>Associated Attributes</title>
<ul>
  <li><attr>suppressTableNameInTitle</attr>  <em>(boolean)</em></li>
  <li><attr>number</attr>  <em>(boolean)</em></li>
</ul>

</section>


<section><title>Description</title>
<!--use <ref> on all component names (other than the one indexed from this file) in this section only-->
  <p>The <tag>table</tag><idx><tag>table</tag></idx> component serves as a component for data rendered in a <tag><ref uri="doenet:doenetID=Bm5kSKo8GvPyl85lokH8_">tabular</ref></tag> format.  Table is a block sectional component, and has the default numbering scheme associated with its parent sectional component. Attributes to change the formatting of the table, such as text alignment and borders, are specified in the <tag>tabular</tag>, the <tag><ref>row</ref></tag>, the <tag><ref>column</ref></tag> and the <tag><ref>cell</ref></tag> components.</p>
</section> 

  
<section><title>Usage Examples</title>

